.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH regin 1  "regin 0.1.0" 
.SH NAME
regin \- AI\-powered Linux server administration agent
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBregin\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Regin — AI\-powered Linux server administration agent.
.PP
Named after the dwarf smith from the Völsunga saga.
.PP
Regin provides an LLM\-backed agent with tool access (shell, file I/O,
web search) for server monitoring, auditing, and operations.
.PP
The daemon (regind) starts automatically. All configuration is stored
in SQLite. No config files needed.
.PP
GETTING STARTED:
  regin config set nanogpt.api_key YOUR_KEY
  regin chat
.PP
See regin(1) and regind(1) for full documentation.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
regin\-chat(1)
Start an interactive chat session with the agent
.TP
regin\-task(1)
Manage and execute operational tasks (skills)
.TP
regin\-runs(1)
Show recent task execution history
.TP
regin\-config(1)
Manage agent configuration
.TP
regin\-memory(1)
Manage the agent\*(Aqs long\-term memory
.TP
regin\-incident(1)
Manage incidents (ITIL): unplanned interruptions or degradations
.TP
regin\-change(1)
Manage changes (ITIL): documented modifications to systems
.TP
regin\-problem(1)
Manage problems (ITIL): root causes behind recurring incidents
.TP
regin\-desired(1)
Inspect the desired (to\-be) state per domain (FEAT\-033)
.TP
regin\-metrics(1)
Show CSI metrics: KPIs + the cost\-vs\-reliability objective (FEAT\-050)
.TP
regin\-filters(1)
Inspect notice filters that suppress known noise before the LLM (FEAT\-052)
.TP
regin\-mode(1)
Show regin\*(Aqs effective operating mode: org (supervisor) vs standalone (FEAT\-041)
.TP
regin\-posture(1)
Show the adaptive autonomy posture and the evidence behind it (FEAT\-040)
.TP
regin\-greeting(1)
Show the login greeting: health + parked items needing a decision (FEAT\-043)
.TP
regin\-push(1)
Active push for critical items (opt\-in, off by default) (FEAT\-044)
.TP
regin\-checks(1)
List active derived (promoted) deterministic checks (FEAT\-051)
.TP
regin\-audit(1)
Run the periodic CSI self\-audit now and file its findings (FEAT\-055)
.TP
regin\-context(1)
Show or set the per\-repo context (stored in regin\*(Aqs own DB, keyed by repo path)
.TP
regin\-bus(1)
Messaging bus: send · inbox (role@cave, via the cave inbox/outbox files)
.TP
regin\-persona(1)
Show the active role persona (REGIN_PERSONA) and its capability ceiling
.TP
regin\-meeting(1)
Chair a meeting: collect inbox reports → compile minutes → emit to dvalin
.TP
regin\-plan(1)
Run the individual planning cycle (aggregate When/Which → plan; emit upward)
.TP
regin\-foreman(1)
Foreman mode: drain the inbox, run cave\-tasks on local workers, hand over
.TP
regin\-skill(1)
Skill packages: install a regin\-*\-skills package · list installed
.TP
regin\-deputy(1)
Deputy mode: assign · show · brief · activate · handback (continuity)
.TP
regin\-ping(1)
Check if the daemon (regind) is running
.TP
regin\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH EXTRA
EXAMPLES:
  regin chat                              Interactive agent session
  regin task list                          List available tasks
  regin task exec security\-audit            Run a task once
  regin task exec disk\-usage daily          Run and schedule daily
  regin memory save fact \*(AqServer runs Ubuntu 24.04\*(Aq
  regin config list                        Show all settings

ENVIRONMENT:
  XDG_RUNTIME_DIR    Socket location (default: $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/regin/)
  RUST_LOG           Log level for diagnostics (e.g. debug, info)
.SH VERSION
v0.1.0
